---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
import { APPS, LAST_UPDATED, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../../legal-config'

const app = APPS[0]
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  appName={app.name}
  lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
  description="How Wardrobe handles app data, photos, account information, purchases, location, and support requests."
>
  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how Wardrobe handles information when you use the app. Wardrobe is
    designed as a personal wardrobe, outfit planning, wishlist, and style-tracking app. This page is
    a practical transparency document and does not replace professional legal advice.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe may collect and store information you choose to add to the app, including wardrobe
    items, item names, categories, brands, colors, notes, barcodes, purchase prices, wishlist target
    prices, product links, photos of clothing, outfits, wear logs, style preferences, trip plans,
    destination names, dates, recommendation feedback, notification preferences, and profile details
    such as name, email, birthday, avatar symbol, and optional profile photo.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you create or sign in to an account, Wardrobe may process account information such as email
    address, authentication status, and a provider user identifier. Passwords and verification flows
    are handled by the authentication provider rather than being stored directly by Wardrobe.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use the Safari share extension, Wardrobe may temporarily store product information from
    the page you shared, such as product URL, suggested name, brand, image URL, price text, currency,
    color, and capture time. This is used to prefill wishlist items.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use camera, photo library, location, notifications, widgets, backups, or purchase
    features, the app and Apple platform services may process the information required to provide
    those features.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe uses information to save your wardrobe, build outfit suggestions, track wears, maintain
    wishlist items, generate style statistics, personalize weather-aware recommendations, prepare
    trip outfit plans, show widgets, schedule reminders you enable, manage account access, process
    Pro entitlements, respond to support requests, and maintain app reliability.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Local Storage, Backups, and Shared App Data</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe stores core wardrobe data on your device using Apple platform storage. The app also
    uses an Apple App Group to share limited data with the widget and share extension, such as the
    look-of-the-day cache, widget thumbnails, and pending wishlist share payloads.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe includes a manual backup feature that exports your wardrobe data to a JSON file. The
    backup can include item photos encoded inside the file. You choose where to save or share that
    backup, such as Files, iCloud Drive, AirDrop, or another destination.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Permissions and Device Features</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe may request access to your photo library so you can choose garment and profile photos,
    camera access so you can scan barcodes or capture item-related content, location access so
    weather-aware recommendations can reflect local conditions, and notification permission so
    reminders and planning nudges can be scheduled. You can manage these permissions in iOS Settings.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe uses Apple services such as StoreKit for purchases and subscriptions, WeatherKit for
    weather-aware recommendations, Photos, Camera, Notifications, Widgets, and App Groups where
    enabled by the operating system.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe uses Firebase for account and backend functionality. Firebase Authentication and
    related Firebase services may process account, authentication, and app data needed to create
    accounts, sign users in, verify email addresses, reset passwords, update passwords, delete
    accounts, and support synced or backend-backed app features. Firebase Analytics is disabled in
    the app configuration reviewed for this policy.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use the share extension or product image preview features, Wardrobe may request image
    data from the product URL or image URL associated with the page you shared.
  </p>

  <h2>7. In-App Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe may offer Pro features through monthly, yearly, or lifetime in-app purchases. Purchases
    and subscriptions are processed through Apple&apos;s App Store using StoreKit. Apple handles
    payment details, billing, subscription management, cancellations, and refund requests. Wardrobe
    receives purchase entitlement information, such as product identifiers and transaction status,
    but does not receive full payment card details.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Local wardrobe data remains on your device until you delete it, delete your account from within
    the app where available, uninstall the app, reset the device, or otherwise remove the data.
    Manual backup files remain wherever you choose to store them until you delete them.
  </p>
  <p>
    Account, purchase, and provider-side technical data may be retained by Apple, Firebase, or other
    involved service providers according to their own policies and legal obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>9. User Rights and Privacy Requests</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, export, restrict, or
    object to certain uses of personal information. You can delete local wardrobe content in the app
    and, where account deletion is available, request deletion of the remote account from the app.
    You can also contact us for privacy requests using the email below.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Security</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe relies on Apple platform security, local device protections, and provider security
    controls for account and purchase services. No method of storage or transmission is completely
    secure, so you should protect your device, Apple ID, and any exported backup files.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Children&apos;s Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe is not directed to children under the age where parental consent is required by
    applicable law. If you believe a child has provided personal information through Wardrobe,
    contact us so we can review the request.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. The latest version will be posted on this
    page with an updated date.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy questions, data requests, or deletion requests, contact <a
      href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a
    >.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
